This paper discusses a reinforcement learning algorithm that gradually expands the policy space, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of reinforcement learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of feature categorization and refinement, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is applied to the game of Tetris, which involves decision-making and strategy, making it relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes experimental results that involve image processing and pattern recognition, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV).
